Description: Fragment of wall and strap handle of East Greek, possibly Aeolian, grey ware pottery closed vessel, probably an oinochoe; handle rounded on inside, flat (slightly concave) on outside; exterior, worn dark grey slip; plastic decoration consisting of horizontal bobbin lug with four incised bars at junction of handle and wall.
Curator's comments: The fabric finds parallels with British Museum 1888, 0601.644.c. This sherd was analysed with NAA by Hans Mommsen (Bonn). The origin of the fabric (NAUK 47) was not identified and considered a chemical singleton.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.003)
